by (Chinonso Peace Mbama)¶

Introduction¶

This data set includes information about individual rides made in Ford bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area.

Based on the assesment of the data, the following quality and tidyness issues were discovered:¶

  1. Start_station_id, start_station_name, end_station_id, end_station_name, members_birth_year and member_gender all have null values in them, all the null values will be dropped.
  2. Columns that are not relevant to the visualisation will be dropped namely: 'start_station_latitude', 'start_station_longitude', 'end_station_latitude', 'end_station_longitude'.
  3. Datatypes for the listed columns will be changed thus: start_station_id': 'str', 'end_station_id': 'str','bike_id': 'str', 'user_type': 'category', 'bike_share_for_all_trip':'category', timestamp to datetime.
  4. Split start_time and end_time to month, week and hour.
  5. Duration_sec will be chieseled to duration_by minutes.
  6. All member_gender identified as others will be dropped

Discuss the distribution(s) of your variable(s) of interest. Were there any unusual points? Did you need to perform any transformations?¶

Duration by minutes had its highest frequency at 8 minutes, week started and week ended shows that most bike rides happend on mondays to fridays. Subsribers were higher users than customers. Males gender were more prominent in the that female gender in the bike rides. Both the hour started and hour ended showed that most rides started and ended within the same time being 8am and 5pm. No unusual points notices and no transformation performed.

Of the features you investigated, were there any unusual distributions? Did you perform any operations on the data to tidy, adjust, or change the form of the data? If so, why did you do this?¶

The member gender identified as 'other' seemed unsual hence it had to be dropped. Also, start and end time were splitted into month, hour and weekday with new columns created to accomodate them. Duration by second was remodified to duration by minutes on a seperate column.
